      • isExpectedResponseStatusCode

        public boolean isExpectedResponseStatusCode​(int statusCode)
        Get whether or not the provided response status code is one of the expected status codes for this Service method.

        1. If the returned int[] is null, then all 2XX status codes are considered as success code. 2. If the returned int[] is not-null, only the codes in the array are considered as success code.

        Specified by:
        isExpectedResponseStatusCode in interface HttpResponseDecodeData
        Parameters:
        statusCode - the status code that was returned in the HTTP response
        Returns:
        whether or not the provided response status code is one of the expected status codes for this Service method

      • getUnexpectedException

        public UnexpectedExceptionInformation getUnexpectedException​(int code)
        Get the UnexpectedExceptionInformation that will be used to generate a RestException if the HTTP response status code is not one of the expected status codes.

        If an UnexpectedExceptionInformation is not found for the status code the default UnexpectedExceptionInformation will be returned.

        Specified by:

        Parameters:
